{% extends '_site/_layout' %} 
{% set breadcrumbs = [ { url: './overview.twig', title: 'Plugins' }, { url: './tabs.twig', title: 'Tabs' } ] %} 
{% block content %}
<div class="section section--default">
  <div class="container">
    {% include '_site/_snippet/_nav/_breadcrumb' %}
    <div class="w8/12">
      <h1>Tabs example</h1>
      <h2>How to setup the tabs:</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc">
        <li>Make a UL and add the class "js-tabs"</li>
        <li>Add buttons to the list items with an attribute "data-panel"</li>
        <li>Make content blocks with class "hidden" and ID's corresponding to the "data-panel" data</li>
        <li>You can add an optional attribute of "data-first-tab" to the UL. This wil render the corresponding tab on load. Default this wil be the first tab.<br />ATTENTION: the first tab is index 0</li>
        <li>You can open a tab via an URL just by giving the ID. "{url}#tab3"</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="section section--default">
  <div class="container">
    <ul class="flex flex-wrap -mx-1 lg:divide-x-2 lg:divide-light lg:m-0 tabs" data-tabs data-first-tab="0" data-update-hash="true">
      <li class="w-full sm:w-1/2 lg:w-auto lg:m-0">
        <button type="button" class="w-full px-5 py-3 text-base font-normal text-primary bg-white-50 aria-selected:bg-primary aria-selected:text-white" data-panel="Tab1">
          Tab 1
